6.5.13.0 — Purpose & Scope
Deep Scan is the platform's multi-axis trip intelligence engine. It synthesizes signals from across a traveler's full itinerary — every leg, every destination, every coverage layer — and returns a structured, confidence-labeled, clause-bound output covering vulnerabilities, opportunities, regulatory requirements, and remediation guidance.
Deep Scan is not itinerary risk modeling. It is not a prediction engine. It does not calculate the probability of a claim being approved, a flight being delayed, or a trip being disrupted. It interprets signals, surfaces what is known, and tells the traveler what to do with that knowledge. Final determination on any coverage or legal outcome rests with the relevant authority or provider.
BOUNDARY STATEMENT (required on every Deep Scan output):  "This briefing is a decision-support tool. It does not constitute legal advice, insurance advice, or a guarantee of coverage. All regulatory information reflects available data at time of scan. Verify entry requirements directly with relevant authorities before departure."

6.5.13.1 — The Ten Axes
Every Deep Scan runs across all applicable axes for every leg and destination in the traveler's confirmed itinerary. Axes 1–8 run for all trips. Axes 9 and 10 run for all international trips. Axis 11 activates when authority-driven disruption signals are detected.

